description:
Do you have a great name or logo for your product or business? Do you have plans of growing your brand, and working to build a solid reputation?

If so,Â you might be wondering how you can cost-efficiently protect your brand, or have more confidence in its strength. How do you make it last so that consumers think highly of your business?

One way to do this is to perform a preliminary trademark search.

The purpose of this course is to give you a good understanding of how to do a preliminary trademark search so that you can make branding decisions on a more informed basis. This will allow you to come up with better names and stronger brands, while reducing attorney fees later on down the line.
title: DIY Trademark Searching
